<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="779" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/8: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-26T16:00:00-05:00">July 26, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>80. Junta consists of President of Senate and Montero and Blanche of last
                            week’s Cabinet. The one uncertain element is still army, which continues
                            loyal to Ibañez, who now announces that he has temporarily withdrawn
                            from office. Crowds have gathered in the main avenue and in front of the
                            Embassy but there are no disorders. No Americans nor American interests
                            have been molested.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>